pullRequest.body:
In this PR, we ported a part of Andrew Yang's lean3 repository at [this repository](https://github.com/erdOne/lean-AG-morphisms), which is appoved by @erdOne after his discussion with @chrisflav . 

Andrew defined `Ideal.primeHeight` and `Ideal.height` in this repository (it's at /dimension_theory/height), we ported this, changed the definition of `Ideal.primeHeight` to  `Order.height (âŸ¨I, hIâŸ© : PrimeSpectrum R)` and ported some basic lemmas about it.

Co-authored-by: 
@erdOne 
@Xuchun-Li <li.xuchun@qq.com>
@jjdishere <emailboxofjjd@163.com>
@Blackfeather007 <2100017455@stu.pku.edu.cn>

/-- An ideal has finite height if it is either the unit ideal or its height is finite.
We include the unit ideal in order to have the instance `IsNoetherianRing R â†’ FiniteHeight I`. -/
class Ideal.FiniteHeight : Prop where
```

noncomputable def ringKrullDim (R : Type*) [CommRing R] : WithBot â„•âˆž :=
```

```suggestion
    Ideal.FiniteHeight I â†” I = âŠ¤ âˆ¨ I.height < âŠ¤ := by
```
The statement should be indented by 4 spaces. Same below.
Just reminding that the statement (the thing after `:` and before `:=`) should be indented with 4 spaces if it is on the new line.

```suggestion
* `Ideal.height` : The height of an ideal. We defined it as the infimum of the `primeHeight` of the
minimal prime ideals of I.
```
Or maybe "over". To me, "minimal prime ideals containing I" sounds like minimal prime ideals of `R` (over `0`) containing `I`.

```suggestion
@[simp]
theorem Ideal.height_top : (âŠ¤ : Ideal R).height = âŠ¤ := by
```
This file has recently moved. Please merge master and replace this with `Mathlib.RingTheory.Spectrum.Prime.Defs` (or `.Basic`)

```suggestion
of it. -/
```

```suggestion
    I.height < âŠ¤ :=
  lt_of_le_of_ne le_top (Ideal.height_ne_top hI)
```
Also, I am not sure if we want both `height_ne_top` and `height_lt_top`. What do you think @erdOne ?
We don't need both but IMO there's no harm keeping it.

```suggestion
In this file, we define the height of a prime ideal and the height of an ideal.
```
Also below. In general, we write the module docstrings in present tense.

```suggestion
* `Ideal.primeHeight` : The height of a prime ideal $\mathfrak{p}$. We define it as the supremum of the lengths of strictly decreasing chains of prime ideals below it.
```
(copied from the docstring of the definition). Maybe also mention that it is implemented via `Order.height`? I think we expect the user to also use the `Order.height` API for this definition.

```suggestion
/-- The height of an ideal is defined as the infimum of the heights of its minimal prime ideals. -/
```
